ntent":"Place water and coconut milk in mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket then weigh in rice and desiccated coconut. Rinse <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Place Varoma dish into position and weigh in chicken, leaving some holes unobstructed for steam to circulate. Cover Varoma and cook <b>20 min\/100°C\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Set covered Varoma aside and remove simmering basket with aid of spatula. Transfer cooked rice to a large bowl and cover to keep warm."},{"content":"Remove Varoma lid and stir chicken with spatula to ensure even cooking."},{"content":"Insert Varoma tray, place Varoma back into position then weigh in baby sweetcorn. Cover Varoma and cook <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Set covered Varoma aside and empty mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place reserved peanut sauce, reserved steamed chicken, reserved cooked baby sweetcorn and sugar snap peas in mixing bowl then cook <b>10 min\/110°C\/\/speed <b>."},{"content":"Divide coconut rice between serving bowls, ladle over peanut chicken then garnish with chopped peanuts and coriander. Serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["After a long day at work when the takeaway menus are calling, give this quick and tasty Thai dish a go. Steamed chicken and veggies are served in a gorgeously creamy peanut sauce accompanied by fragrant coconut rice - the perfect family fakeaway!","Sriracha sauce is a Thai hot sauce made from a paste of chillies, vinegar, garlic, sugar and salt. It is often used as a dipping sauce, but can also be eaten on burgers or eggs. If sriracha sauce is not available, substitute with chilli sauce of choice."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","6 portions"]}